    <h1>Terms of the licence</h1>

    <p class="nhsuk-lede-text">This is a licence for specific Frutiger fonts for NHS organisations only. By registering for this licence, you can get access to authorised versions of the Frutiger font.</p>
    <p>Before you can download and use the Frutiger font under NHS England's licence, you must read and agree to these terms.</p>
    <p>NHS England has a licence for 3 weights of the Frutiger font, which is the brand font for the NHS. Monotype owns the font software and other elements of the font which are protected by intellectual property rights. We call these the "font" for short in these terms.</p>
    <h2>Who can register for a licence</h2>
    <p>NHS organisations in England can register to use the font for free under this licence.</p>
    <p>You do not need to register if your team is part of NHS England.</p>
    <details class="nhsuk-details">
      <summary class="nhsuk-details__summary">
        <span class="nhsuk-details__summary-text">
        Legal effects of these terms for different NHS organisations
        </span>
      </summary>
      <div class="nhsuk-details__text">
      <p>The legal effects of the terms of the licence depend on what type of organisation you are.</p>
      <p>If your organisation is an NHS organisation covered by section 9 of the <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2006/41/section/9">National Health Service Act 2006</a>, such as an NHS trust or an integrated care board (ICB), this agreement is an "NHS contract" as defined by that section. But this licence should still be treated as seriousnessly as if it were legally binding.</p>
      <p>For other NHS organisations, such as foundation trusts, this licence is legally binding.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <h2>The fonts covered by this licence</h2>
    <p>The licence covers Frutiger in 3 weights:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Frutiger 65 Bold</li>
      <li>Frutiger 55 Roman</li>
      <li>Frutiger 45 Light, but the licence does not cover using this weight in an app</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This licence covers the font version and format that NHS England bought in December 2024. It does not cover any newer versions of the font.</p>
    <p>You are allowed to use the font as described in this licence alongside other organisations we licence to.</p>

    <h3>Other Frutiger fonts</h3>
    <p>You must buy your own licence if you want to use:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>any other font or font weight, such as Frutiger Italic</li>
      <li>Frutiger 45 Light in a mobile downloadable app</li>
      <li>Frutiger in a way that is not covered in this licence</li>
    </ul>
    <p>If you have a licence for other Frutiger fonts, you must follow the terms of those licences.</p>

    <h2>What you can and cannot do with this licence</h2>
    <p>You must:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>manage access to the font and only let people in your organisation or your suppliers use it for your organisation's purposes</li>
      <li>make sure everyone you allow to use the font is aware of and agrees to comply with these terms</li>
      <li>only use the font for the specific purposes and use cases set out in these terms</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You are responsible for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>your users' and suppliers' use of the fonts and compliance with this licence</li>
        <li>any unauthorised access to the font on your or their systems</li>
        <li>any claims by Monotype (the owner of the font) for your, your users' and your suppliers' misuse of the font</li>
      </ul>
    <p>You must not license, assign or transfer the font to another organisation or give anyone outside your organisation access to it, with the exception of suppliers who are using it for your organisation's purposes. They must not grant any further licences.</p>
    <p>NHS England is not responsible for any losses, claims or liabilities arising out of your, your users' or suppliers' use of the font on your or their systems.</p>
    <p>You cannot use Monotype's font platform or its app to get these fonts. You can only get them by registering here.</p>
    <h3>Suppliers</h3>
    <p>You can give your suppliers access to the font to produce NHS branded goods or services for you.</p>
    <p>You must make sure that they:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>agree to these terms</li>
      <li>only use the font to provide goods or services to you (and not for their own use)</li>
      <li>do not allow anyone else to use the font</li>
      <li>delete any font files you have given them at the end of the job</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>The font files</h3>
    <p>You must not:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>change the font or use it to make other fonts</li>
      <li>embed the font software code in open source software in a way that makes it publicly available</li>
      <li>take out or change the font metadata</li>
      <li>transfer or use the font outside the UK</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Using the font in different products, systems and services</h3>
    <details class="nhsuk-details">
      <summary class="nhsuk-details__summary">
        <span class="nhsuk-details__summary-text">
          Online services, including websites
        </span>
      </summary>
      <div class="nhsuk-details__text">
        <p>You can use the font to write text and create forms on websites you control.</p>
        <p>You must make sure people cannot download, reformat or use the font code.</p> 
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="nhsuk-details">
